"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669080","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-12","<p>I refer the hon.Member to the Written Statement I made on 18 April 2016 (HCWS678).</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-01-12T16:08:22.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669080/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669080/answer","Hansard Extract 18 April 2016, HCWS678.docx","HCWS678 - Written Statement on Armed Forces Update","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669080/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-06","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the Government's policy is on requiring a debate in the House on a substantive motion prior to any planned deployment of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","58695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669081","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>Health and social care policies in Scotland are devolved, and the policy of free personal and nursing care is a matter for the Scottish Government.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-01-11T13:17:20.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669081/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669081/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669081/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-01-06","Age: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, if he will support the introduction of Frank's Law to prevent age discrimination against those aged under 65.","false","Biography information for Gavin Robinson","Belfast East","Gavin Robinson","58705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669082","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency does not have a defining boundary for (a) ‘London’ and therefore cannot provide an average waiting time figure.</p><p> </p><p>The official waiting time is based on more than 10% of test slots being available in an individual test centre. The official measure is not a weighted average and does not take account of volumes of tests we deliver at any given test centre.</p><p> </p><p>As at 09.01.17, the average waiting time for a practical driving test in (b) England and (c) Hornsey and Wood Green constituency is:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>6.7 weeks</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wood Green driving test centre</p></td><td><p>15 weeks</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T13:50:18.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669082/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669082/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669082/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the average waiting time is for a practical driving test in (a) London, (b) England and (c) Hornsey and Wood Green constituency.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","58691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669083","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) is taking a number of actions to improve the process of securing practical driving tests by increasing the number of available slots.</p><p> </p><p>It:</p><ul><li>continually monitors demand and staffing levels to make sure it deploys the right number of examiners to each location and consequently, more examiners have been recruited.</li><li>launched a successful initiative to offer examiner testing over the October half-term, which led to an extra 1,000 test slots being available in this period.</li><li>is running a ‘winter hours’ initiative between 1 December 2016 and 31 March 2017 to offer weekend testing and extra hours for part-time examiners to increase test slots.</li><li>is reducing the number of motorcycle slots by 10% to free up slots for car testing to take advantage of the fact that bike testing naturally declines by 20% during the winter.</li><li>has stopped taxi driver assessments as of 31 December 2016, which has freed up considerable examiner resource.</li></ul><p> </p><p>DVSA publishes all details of short notice cancellations and extra appointments being offered at local test centres on its online booking service on GOV.UK and on its twitter account: @DVSA_HelpMe</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T13:54:30.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669083/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669083/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669083/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to improve the efficiency of the process for securing a practical driving test.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","58692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669084","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>This money comes from Network Rail’s existing budget and work has been carried out on replacing worn tracks, hiring extra staff, improving train dispatch times, providing more Network Rail rapid response teams, accelerating track maintenance programmes, additional signal supervisors, improving bridge strike prevention, investment to speed up and identify the causes of delay and improve responses to delays, and improvements in depot flows.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-16T13:39:33.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669084/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669084/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669084/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Railways: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, (a) how much of and (b) on what the £20 million fund managed by Chris Gibb to achieve improvements to rail services has been spent to date.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","58763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669085","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>Officials from the Maritime and Coastguard Agency are in regular contact with their counterparts in the Scottish Government on the subject of ship-to-ship transfer proposals that affect Scottish waters, and on the development of the policy itself.</p><p> </p><p>With regard to the ship-to-ship transfer licence application in the Cromarty Firth, in the event that a revised application is submitted we fully intend that the Scottish Government will be formally consulted.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-11T16:40:19.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669085/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669085/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669085/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Shipping: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will formally consult the Scottish Government on ship-to-ship transfer proposals that affect Scottish waters.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","58934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669086","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The number of passenger journeys made on local bus services in London and England from 1970 to 2015/16 can be found in table BUS0103 at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/bus01-local-bus-passenger-journeys#table-bus0103" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/bus01-local-bus-passenger-journeys#table-bus0103</a>. However, estimates of the number of passenger journeys on local bus services that operate a school service are not produced.</p><p> </p><p>The Department’s National Travel Survey collects information on travel to school. The number of trips to and from school by local bus per child per year in England can be found in table NTS0613 at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/nts06-age-gender-and-modal-breakdown#table-nts0613" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/nts06-age-gender-and-modal-breakdown#table-nts0613</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T15:17:39.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669086/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669086/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669086/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Bus Services: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of trends in usage of public bus school services.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","58901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669087","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The government has announced that it intends to invest over £1bn upgrading the A66 between the M6 and the A1, to create the first new continuous dual carriageway link across the Pennines in 45 years. The Port of Heysham was misplaced in figure 1.1 as a result of a consultant error, and the document will be updated shortly to address this.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-16T11:31:48.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669087/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669087/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669087/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Roads: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Northern Trans-Pennine Routes strategic study: stage 3 report, paragraph 1.4.1, published on 28 November 2016, for what reasons there is an error for the position of the Port of Heysham on the map in figure 1.1.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","58881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669088","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p><strong> </strong>This is an operational matter for the train operator. The Class 37 train is due to be replaced from the Northern fleet by the end of 2019.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-16T11:51:51.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669088/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669088/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669088/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Railways: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the reliability of the Class 37 locomotives that run between Barrow and Preston; and how many journeys were delayed or cancelled in (a) 2016 and (b) 2015 due to engine failure.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","58858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669089","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Department’s investment board considered Southeastern’s proposal in December 2016. We have concluded the plans are not deliverable as previously proposed, principally because depot-related costs have escalated significantly. As a result, the Department has asked Southeastern and GTR (both owned by Govia) to work together to provide alternative workable solutions for offering additional extra capacity in Southeastern for 2017, including credible stabling options.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-16T13:26:45.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669089/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669089/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669089/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Southeastern: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 8 December 2016 to Question 55749, what progress has been made by his Department's investment board in considering the business case submitted by Southeastern Railway for additional rolling stock.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","58809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669090","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>All new trains being introduced to the Northern franchise will be compliant with modern accessibility standards. Existing trains which are operated by Northern are required to meet these standards by 2020.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-16T11:37:27.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669090/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669090/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669090/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Northern: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of compliance with disability legislation of railway rolling stock operated by Northern in Lancashire and Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","58800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669091","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Northern franchise will be transformed thanks to enormous investment in trains – making Northern into an engine for economic growth in the north of England. The operator will oversee the complete removal of the outdated and unpopular Pacers by the end of 2019. It will also invest £400 million in 281 brand new air-conditioned carriages resulting in 98 new-build trains, some of which will serve destinations in both Lancashire and Cumbria. For the remaining fleet a refurbishment will be carried out which will include as a minimum the fitment of passenger information systems, compliance with accessibility regulations and free Wi-Fi to passengers.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-16T11:47:43.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669091/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669091/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669091/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Northern: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of the age of railway rolling stock operated by Northern in Lancashire and Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","58801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669092","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Department publishes an annual index of local bus fares from 1995 onwards.</p><p> </p><p>This table can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/35990/bus0405.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/35990/bus0405.xls</a></p><p> </p><p>This index covers operators of local bus services. The Department does not produce an index for local bus operators that operate a school service.</p><p>The bus market outside London is deregulated and decisions regarding setting the level of fares, is primarily a commercial matter for bus operators.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T15:23:38.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669092/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669092/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669092/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Bus Services: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of trends in the cost of public bus services on school services to passengers.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","58802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669093","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Department publishes an annual index of local bus fares from 1995 onwards.</p><p> </p><p>This table can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/35990/bus0405.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/35990/bus0405.xls</a></p><p> </p><p>Between 1997 and 2010 local bus fares in England rose annually by 2.2% on average in real terms. Between 2010 and 2016, the comparative figure is 1.2%.</p><p> </p><p>The bus market outside London is deregulated and decisions regarding setting the level of fares, is primarily a commercial matter for bus operators.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T15:29:17.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669093/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669093/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669093/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of trends in the cost to passengers of public bus services.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","58803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669094","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>The Government has had recent discussions with Midland Expressway in order to renew an existing agreement to provide resilience to the Strategic Road Network in exceptional circumstances. General usage on the Toll road is a matter for the operator.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-11T16:44:45.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669094/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669094/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669094/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","M6 Toll","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with the Midlands Expressway on usage of the M6 Toll Road.","false","Biography information for Mr Khalid Mahmood","Birmingham, Perry Barr","Mr Khalid Mahmood","58818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669095","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The draft Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy was published on 27 March 2016 for public consultation and we hope to publish the final Strategy shortly. The Department’s guidance in <em>Local Transport Note 2/08: Cycle Infrastructure Design</em> is comprehensive and allows councils to design good, safe schemes that encourages cycling across all demographics. The Department will consider how to refresh this guidance to take account of the new facilities to encourage cycling introduced in the Traffic Signs Regulations and General Directions 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Furthermore, the Department is in the process of drafting an Accessibility Action Plan which seeks to address the barriers faced by disabled people in accessing public transport and the wider public realm. We have also begun the process of inviting proposals for a new programme of work to update our guidance on “Inclusive Mobility”. As part of this project we will also update our guidance on the use of tactile paving surfaces.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T12:03:26.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669095/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669095/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669095/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will include in his Department's forthcoming Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy a commitment to create new road environment design standards to encourage cycle use among (a) children and young people, (b) women, (c) older people and (d) people with disabilities.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","58966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669096","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>My Department regards air services to and from UK as an economic priority, essential for the creation of jobs and growth.</p><p> </p><p>We have the world’s third largest aviation market and are working to maintain and expand it. My officials are active at international, multilateral and bilateral levels to support the expansion of air services.</p><p> </p><p>Last year my officials engaged with over 25 countries, ranging from China and Russia to the Bahamas, to renew and update the UK’s air services arrangements. These new arrangements will support the creation of long haul air services to airports across the UK, as well as maximising business opportunities for UK airlines and airports.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-16T17:12:44.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669096/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669096/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669096/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to support the creation of new long-haul air services to airports across the UK to support international trade as part of the new Aviation Policy Framework.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","58954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669097","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>High Speed Two is being developed in a way that supports the Northern Powerhouse to develop better connectivity between northern cities. The Command Paper <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/568208/high-speed-two-crewe-manchester-west-midlands-leeds-web-version.pdf" target="_blank"><em>High Speed Two: From Crewe to Manchester, the West Midlands to Leeds and beyond</em></a> published in November 2016 sets this out in some detail.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T13:33:37.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669097/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669097/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669097/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","High Speed 2 Railway Line: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether it is Government policy that the High Speed 2 and Northern Powerhouse rail projects are not developed in isolation; and whether he plans to integrate those two schemes.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","58955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669098","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>The below table shows the best estimate of the number of road accident casualties in Great Britain that have been (a) seriously and (b) slightly injured that have been unreported to the police for the last three years.</p><p> </p><p>Thousands of casualties (estimates rounded to the nearest 10 thousand)</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Injury severity</p></td><td><p>Best estimate of unreported casualties</p></td><td><p>Lower estimate</p></td><td><p>Upper estimate</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>2011-15</p></td><td><p>Serious</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Slight</p></td><td><p>460</p></td><td><p>380</p></td><td><p>540</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>2010-14</p></td><td><p>Serious</p></td><td><p>70</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Slight</p></td><td><p>480</p></td><td><p>390</p></td><td><p>550</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>2009-13</p></td><td><p>Serious</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Slight</p></td><td><p>460</p></td><td><p>380</p></td><td><p>540</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The unreported road casualties are based on questions asked in the National Travel Survey (NTS) which are based on a sample survey and are subject to uncertainty resulting from small sample sizes. The estimates are created from data collected from the NTS over five years to produce a robust statistic. All estimates are rounded to the nearest ten thousand to reflect the uncertainty.</p><p> </p><p>As the total number of road accident casualties is subject to considerable uncertainty, the lower and upper estimates provided above indicate the range in which the precise number of unreported casualties is likely to fall.</p><p> </p><p>All of the changes between the years are within the upper and lower estimate range. This indicates that the apparent changes are as a result of sampling error rather than a change in the number of casualties.</p><p> </p><p>These figures are also available within table <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/555469/ras54004.ods" target="_blank">RAS54004</a>.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-11T11:50:26.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669098/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669098/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669098/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of road accident casualties that have been (a) seriously and (b) slightly injured that have been unreported to the police in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","58963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669099","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy Consultation, published on 27 March 2016, set out how we will help local bodies to take a more strategic approach to improving conditions for cycling and walking by issuing guidelines on the preparation of Local Cycling and Walking Infrastructure Plans (LCWIPs). LCWIPs will help ensure that consideration is given to cycling and walking within both planning and transport policies and strategies at the local level. We hope to publish the LCWIP guidance shortly.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T12:11:40.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669099/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669099/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669099/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-06","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will include in his Department's forthcoming Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy a commitment to review how the planning system (a) supports and (b) fails to support (i) the creation of quality cycling conditions and (ii) improvements to existing cycling conditions.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","58965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669100","Wales Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>The Department for Transport and the Wales Office are working closely with the Welsh Government to facilitate their ongoing procurement process for the Wales and Borders rail franchise and to finalise these arrangements – including the transfer of franchising functions – during 2017.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-01-11T15:10:42.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669100/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669100/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669100/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-01-06","Wales and Borders Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, pursuant to the Answer of 14 October 2016 to Question 46772, what progress has been made on procurement of the Wales and Borders Rail franchise.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","58946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669101","Women and Equalities","false","2017-01-16","<p>We intend to issue the consultation shortly at which point it will run for 12 weeks.</p><p> </p><p>[Caste is an extremely sensitive and emotive subject. This is the first ever public consultation on the matter and it is vital that we get the details and content of the consultation right].</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-01-16T17:53:01.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669101/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669101/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669101/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-01-06","Castes: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, when the consultation on caste discrimination announced on 2 September 2016 will commence.","false","Biography information for Mr Graham Allen","Nottingham North","Mr Graham Allen","58872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669102","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-11","<p>The Jobseeker’s Allowance Sanctions Early Warning Trial in Scotland ran until September 2016 and involved approximately 6,500 claimants. Data were collected throughout the trial period to assess the extent to which the warning trial affected sanction decisions. Qualitative interviews are currently being undertaken with a sample of these claimants to gain an understanding of how the new process affected claimant behaviour. The trial has now finished and a full evaluation is being undertaken. An interim report was published on 20 December 2016 and the final report will be published around Spring 2017. Findings from the trial will inform any decisions on future roll-out. The link to the interim report is posted below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=research-and-analysis&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-work-pensions&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=&amp;commit=Refresh+results" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=research-and-analysis&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-work-pensions&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=&amp;commit=Refresh+results</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-01-11T14:39:36.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669102/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669102/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669102/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-06","Jobseeker's Allowance: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants in Scotland were covered by the jobseeker's allowance sanctions early warning trial between March and September 2016; and what plans he has to extend that trial across the UK.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","58845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669103","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-11","<p>I would refer my Hon Friend to PQ55481, my previous answer to this question given on 2 December 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-11T15:25:40.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669103/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669103/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669103/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-06","Carer's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans the Government has to reform the earnings limit applied to the carer's allowance.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Prisk","Hertford and Stortford","Mr Mark Prisk","58823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669104","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-11","<p>Disability Living Allowance (DLA) has two components: care and mobility. The care component has three payment rates and the mobility component two. There are therefore eleven payment rates in total. It is not clear to what ‘higher-level disability living allowance’ refers.</p><p> </p><p>Various statistics on DLA to Personal Independence Payment (PIP) reassessment outcomes are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-independence-payment-april-2013-to-october-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-independence-payment-april-2013-to-october-2016</a></p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","58949 ; 58950 ; 58951","2017-01-11T15:32:21.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669104/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669104/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/669104/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-06","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people not previously in receipt of higher-level disability living allowance were awarded the mobility element of personal independence payments by (a) quarter and (b) region in 2016.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","58948"
