"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662821","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Department is not aware of any such applications but this question should be addressed to Lancashire County Council.</p>","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","58441","2017-01-09T17:02:43.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662821/answer","Biography information for Andrew Percy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662821/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662821/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-20","Regeneration: Heysham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what applications have been submitted to Lancashire County Council on regeneration in South Heysham.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","58440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662822","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-01-12","<p>I can confirm my department currently does not have the facility to allow staff to join a credit union through payroll deductions. Staff can still make arrangements to contribute to a credit union via direct debit.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-01-12T16:10:19.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662822/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662822/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662822/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-20","Department for Communities and Local Government: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department permits its employees to join a credit union through payroll deductions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","58446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662823","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-17","<p>DCMS staff can make arrangements to contribute to a credit union via direct debit.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-17T12:01:49.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662823/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662823/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662823/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether her Department permits its employees to join a credit union through payroll deductions; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","58447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662824","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>A decision will be made in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T14:33:32.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662824/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662824/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662824/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Social Media: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will make it her policy to review the adequacy of the Electronic Commerce (EC Directive) Regulations 2002 in so far as they relate to social media platforms after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","58389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662825","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Government's formal response will be published shortly.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T15:25:44.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662825/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662825/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662825/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Arts: Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 12 December 2016 to Question 56474, if she will provide the answer sought in that Question on what discussions she has had with Ministers of HM Treasury on the potential effect on freelance creative workers of HM Revenue and Customs proposals that self-employed workers update their tax quarterly; and what steps she plans to take to address the concerns of those workers.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","58630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662826","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>This is a matter for Ofcom. DCMS has noted Ofcom's competition and consumer assessment, as set out in its successive consultations on the forthcoming auction of 2.3 and 3.4 GHz spectrum.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T13:10:46.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662826/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662826/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662826/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Mobile Phones: Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether her Department has made an assessment of the potential effect of a 30 per cent cap on mobile spectrum on (a) competition and (b) prices for consumers.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","58550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662827","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>Government continues to engage intensively with industry, including major social media companies, and charities through the UK Council for Child Internet Safety (UKCCIS) a multi-stakeholder forum representing over 200 organisations with an interest in internet safety. UKCCIS has published a guide for providers of social media and interactive services to help make their platforms safer for children and young people under 18. UKCCIS is working to ensure this guide influences policy and practice by online service providers both within and outside the UK. Government expects industry to review and improve its child internet safety provisions as technology changes.</p><p> </p><p>Leading providers report on their online safety practices voluntarily as part of the safety framework of the ICT Coalition for Children Online: <a href="http://ictcoalition.org/" target="_blank">http://ictcoalition.org/</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T14:12:46.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662827/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662827/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662827/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Social Media: Harassment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 19 October 2016 to Question 48756, what steps the Government plans to take to ensure that its expectations for social media providers to have robust processes in place to deal with abusive content are met.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","58499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662828","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>The data collected by the Libraries Taskforce in relation to statutory and non-statutory public libraries will be published in due course.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2017-01-09T14:27:13.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662828/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662828/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662828/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Public Libraries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the timetable is for the release of data collected by the Libraries Taskforce in relation to statutory and non-statutory public libraries; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","58490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662829","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>Information on the total amount of current and capital expenditure on services by organisation in Yorkshire and the Humber is publically available on gov.uk as part of the Country and Regional Analysis statistical release. This analysis provides a breakdown of government expenditure on services by country/region and covers 2011-12 through to 2015-16. It can be found at the following web link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/country-and-regional-analysis-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/country-and-regional-analysis-2016</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T12:38:25.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662829/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662829/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662829/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much her Department and its arm's-length departmental bodies has spent on (a) staffing, (b) other revenue costs and (c) capital expenditure in the current financial year in Yorkshire and the Humber.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","58625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662830","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>This assessment forms part of Ofcom's competition assessment, which can be found here: https://www.ofcom.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0026/93545/award-of-the-spectrum-bands-consultation.pdf</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T13:13:05.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662830/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662830/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662830/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Mobile Phones: Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effect of UK's distribution of spectrum on competition in the mobile industry.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","58604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662831","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>Efficient use of spectrum is both the Government's aim and a statutory objective for Ofcom in carrying out its spectrum duties. Long term non- or under- use of assigned spectrum by a licensee could be inefficient, depending on the likely alternative use.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T13:14:13.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662831/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662831/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662831/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Mobile Phones: Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will make it her policy to ensure that mobile networks use all of the spectrum holdings available.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","58605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662832","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>Ofcom have addresses the subject here: https://www.ofcom.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0026/93545/award-of-the-spectrum-bands-consultation.pdf</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T13:15:35.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662832/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662832/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662832/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Mobile Phones: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the potential benefits to Scotland of increasing the equality of spectrum holdings among mobile networks.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","58606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662833","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-09","<p>We are funding the clearance of 700 MHz spectrum for additional coverage from around 2020 and we have negotiated new coverage obligations in spectrum licences which will further extend mobile coverage in 2017.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-09T13:16:47.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662833/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662833/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662833/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-20","Mobile Phones: Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps she is taking to ensure that the UK's distribution of spectrum ensures (a) coverage and (b) competition across the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","58607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662834","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-10","<p>The Ministry of Defence is actively engaged in initial operational test and evaluation planning as part of a joint F-35 test team with the United States. The plan is subject to appropriate scrutiny but no decisions have been taken on a phased start to testing.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-10T16:09:52.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662834/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662834/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662834/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of the potential merits of a phase start for Initial Operational Test and Evaluation for the F35B Lightning II.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","58645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662835","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-10","<p>Air-to-air range instrumentation is a test asset used on previous aircraft programmes. Instrumentation components integrated within F-35B Lightning test aircraft will be tested before initial operational test and evaluation starts. This is unrelated to Block 3F testing.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-10T16:08:23.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662835/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662835/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662835/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the F35B Lightning II is due to complete air-to-air instrumentation testing before the end of Block 3F testing.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","58646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662836","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-10","<p>Analysis of the global frigate market included identification of ships within the 2,000 to 6,000 tonne displacement range which are likely to be in service or developed over the next 20 years.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-10T16:12:31.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662836/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662836/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662836/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Type 31 Frigates: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 16 December 2016 to Question 57632, what assessment has been made of the identity of the principal competitors for Type 31 frigates in the global export market.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","58644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662837","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-09","<p>Yes.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-09T16:04:18.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662837/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662837/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662837/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft: Scandinavia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether F35 Joint Strike Fighters from (a) the Netherlands, (b) Denmark and (c) Norway will be able to operate from UK airfields to conduct exercises.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","58642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662838","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-10","<p>The F-35 System Development and Demonstration programme is planned to conclude on completion of Block 3F testing. UK F-35B Lightning initial operating capability is scheduled to be at Block 3F standard and remains on track for 2018.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-10T16:09:10.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662838/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662838/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662838/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 16 December 2016 to Question 57052, on joint strike fighter aircraft, whether he has made an assessment of the potential effect that the ending of the System Development and Demonstration programme will have on the proposed initial operating capability for the UK F-35B in 2018 upon completion of Block 3F testing.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","58643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662840","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-09","<p>Given the unprecedented number and complexity of the Iraq investigations, it would be disproportionately costly to analyse the time taken to resolve allegations. On current plans, IHAT will have completed its work by the end of 2019, having dealt with over 3,300 allegations received since it was set up in November 2010. The IHAT has made significant progress and has already disposed of 70% of these allegations.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-09T16:04:57.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662840/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662840/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662840/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Iraq Historic Allegations Team","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average time taken to resolve a case by the Iraq Historic Allegations Team is.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","58616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662841","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-10","<p>UK-manufactured BL755 cluster munitions were supplied to Saudi Arabia under a government-to-government agreement signed in 1986. The final delivery against this agreement was made in 1989.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-10T16:06:52.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662841/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662841/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662841/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Arms Trade: Cluster Munitions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what information his Department holds on the sale of UK-manufactured cluster bombs to non-NATO countries between 1980 and 1995.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","58374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662842","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-12","<p>UK Armed Forces personnel have had no involvement intraining Saudi armed forces in the use of cluster munitions since the UK signed the Convention on Cluster Munitions in 2008.</p><p>The UK has provided training courses for Royal Saudi Air Force personnel and artillery training for the Royal Saudi Land Forces.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","58305","2017-01-12T16:09:06.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662842/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662842/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662842/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Saudi Arabia: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department provided training programmes to the Saudi Arabian-led military coalition in (a) air warfare skills and artillery techniques and (b) the use of cluster munitions between 1980 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","58373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662843","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-11","<p>In October 2015, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) launched a facility to make Credit Union services available to UK Regular Armed Forces personnel via payroll deductions. Three chosen Credit Unions are now working together collectively under the banner 'Joining Forces' to provide Service personnel with access to dependable savings facilities and safe, affordable loans. Further details are available from their website:</p><p>http://joiningforcescu.co.uk/</p><p>The MOD does not have an arrangement with a Credit Union for its civilian employees.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-01-11T16:21:00.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662843/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662843/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662843/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","Ministry of Defence: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department permits its employees to join a credit union through payroll deductions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","58448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662844","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-10","<p>The Third Tier Arrangement was last updated on 27 March 2014. The most recent tabletop and field exercises conducted under the auspices of the Arrangement, Exercise DIAMOND DRAGON 2015, were held in Suffolk over the period 30 June to 2 July 2015. The dates and locations of the next tabletop and field exercises are yet to be agreed.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-10T16:10:31.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662844/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662844/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662844/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-20","USA: Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the Third Tier arrangement between the UK and the US for responding to an accident in the UK involving US nuclear weapons was last reviewed and updated; and what the dates and locations of (a) the last and (b) the next scheduled tabletop and field exercises conducted under the auspices of that arrangement are.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","58420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662845","Department for Education","false","2017-01-11","<p>We are currently undertaking evidence gathering and analysis to estimate the potential costs of providing more flexibility for summer born children. However, it is complex and will depend on how we implement any changes, the level of parental take up and whether those children take up free early education.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-01-11T13:37:44.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662845/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662845/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662845/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-20","Schools: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what progress the Minister of State for School Standards has made on assessing the potential costs of changing the Schools Admissions Code to provide more flexibility for summer-born children.","false","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","58432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662846","Department for Education","false","2017-01-24","<p>The department does not currently offer the facility for employees to join a credit union through payroll deductions. We will be considering whether to introduce this as part of our offer to staff.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-01-24T17:45:57.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662846/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662846/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662846/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-20","Department for Education: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether her Department permits its employees to join a credit union through payroll deductions; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","58449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662847","Department for Education","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Department may become aware of financial irregularities in an academy trust through the Education Funding Agency’s annual programme of assurance work or from allegations it receives. We review these, follow up on a case by case basis and maintain a record of verdicts or judgments made by a court. As stated in the answer to Question 55974, we know of one case where a court has found a head teacher or board member guilty of (responsible for) financial irregularity at an academy trust.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-01-09T15:59:06.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662847/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662847/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662847/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-20","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 8 December 2016 to Question 55974, on academies: finance, for what reason her Department is not aware of other judgments.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","58383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662848","Department for Education","false","2017-01-11","<p>Care leavers’ experiences before care mean that as a group they have poorer outcomes than other young people. While the Department does not collect data on the relationship between mental health needs and outcomes, our cross-government care leaver strategy, published in July 2016, is based around five issues care leavers identified as barriers to success, including improved access to health support. We also know from our consultations with care leavers that they often find it difficult to access the right mental health support when they leave care which impacts on other areas of their lives. This includes their engagement in education, employment and training.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Health is represented on a senior Whitehall officials group on care leavers. The Department is working closely with the Department for Health, NHS England and the Expert Working Group to develop the scope of the mental health assessment pilots announced by Lord Nash on 23 November. No decisions have yet been made on the precise scope of the pilots and whether they will cover children in care and care leavers. The terms of reference of the Expert Working Group to develop mental health care pathways for looked after children explicitly include care leavers. We will act on the findings from the Expert Working Group and the mental health assessment pilots.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","58371 ; 58376 ; 58380","2017-01-11T15:08:58.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662848/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662848/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662848/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-20","Children in Care: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the mental health assessment pilots for looked-after children announced by her Department in November 2016 will cover both children in care and care leavers.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","58370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662849","Department for Education","false","2017-01-11","<p>Care leavers’ experiences before care mean that as a group they have poorer outcomes than other young people. While the Department does not collect data on the relationship between mental health needs and outcomes, our cross-government care leaver strategy, published in July 2016, is based around five issues care leavers identified as barriers to success, including improved access to health support. We also know from our consultations with care leavers that they often find it difficult to access the right mental health support when they leave care which impacts on other areas of their lives. This includes their engagement in education, employment and training.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Health is represented on a senior Whitehall officials group on care leavers. The Department is working closely with the Department for Health, NHS England and the Expert Working Group to develop the scope of the mental health assessment pilots announced by Lord Nash on 23 November. No decisions have yet been made on the precise scope of the pilots and whether they will cover children in care and care leavers. The terms of reference of the Expert Working Group to develop mental health care pathways for looked after children explicitly include care leavers. We will act on the findings from the Expert Working Group and the mental health assessment pilots.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","58370 ; 58376 ; 58380","2017-01-11T15:08:58.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662849/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662849/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662849/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-20","Children in Care: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the Expert Working Group for looked-after children's mental health plans to publish recommendations on mental health assessments for both looked-after children and care leavers.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","58371"
