re, believe it would provide value for money for the taxpayer to collate information on the cost of all school closures.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","58494 ; 58495 ; 58496","2017-01-09T16:01:49.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662865/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662865/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662865/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-20","Schools: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 8 December 2016 to Question 55853, for what reasons her Department does not record centrally the costs of school closures.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","58497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662866","Department for Education","false","2017-01-10","<p>This Government takes any form of violence and sexual harassment in universities seriously. In November 2015, Universities UK was asked by Government to convene a sexual violence and harassment taskforce<strong>. </strong>The Taskforce reported its findings in October 2016 in the report ‘Changing the Culture’, which can be found on their website at: <a href="http://www.universitiesuk.ac.uk/policy-and-analysis/reports/Documents/2016/changing-the-culture.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.universitiesuk.ac.uk/policy-and-analysis/reports/Documents/2016/changing-the-culture.pdf</a></p><p>The Taskforce made a series of recommendations to universities on preventing and responding to sexual harassment, sexual violence and hate crime in universities. Staff to student harassment and sexual abuse is covered as part of the institution-wide response recommendation, which applies to staff as well as students. Universities UK plan to establish more baseline evidence on this issue and report later this year.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-01-10T09:18:01.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662866/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662866/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662866/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-20","Universities: Sexual Harassment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will make an assessment of the merits of launching an inquiry into the levels of staff-to-student sexual harassment in universities.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","58641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662867","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-09","<p>As part of the review of animal establishment licensing schemes, the Government is proposing to remove the licence exemptions in the Pet Animals Act 1951. These exemptions are for those in the business of selling either pedigree animals that have been bred by them or the offspring of an animal that has been kept by them as a pet, for instance, the offspring of their non-pedigree pet cat. We will be publishing our ‘Next Steps’ document on the proposals shortly.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-01-09T14:58:42.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662867/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662867/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662867/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Cats: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 8 December 2016 to Question 56069, what plans the Government has to remove the exemption from licensing requirements of people repeatedly selling kittens bred from their non-pedigree pet cat, currently in place under the provisions of the Pet Animals Act 1951, within new regulations governing the sale of pet animals made under the Animal Welfare Act 2006.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","58493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662868","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-11","<p>We meet regularly at Ministerial and official level with representatives of the industry to discuss key issues and opportunities for the UK dairy sector.</p><p> </p><p>I am aware of concerns regarding recommendations on the consumption of dairy products in the Eatwell Guide produced by Public Health England (PHE) in March 2016. PHE has prepared a report detailing the approaches, methods and decisions made in developing the Eatwell Guide. The report “From Plate to Guide: What, why and how for the Eatwell model” is available on the PHE website.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","58416 ; 58435","2017-01-11T15:25:59.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662868/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662868/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662868/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Dairy Farming: Health Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Health on the effect of the linear programming model used to develop the Eatwell Guide on the dairy and milk industry.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","58434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662869","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-11","<p>We meet regularly at Ministerial and official level with representatives of the industry to discuss key issues and opportunities for the UK dairy sector.</p><p> </p><p>I am aware of concerns regarding recommendations on the consumption of dairy products in the Eatwell Guide produced by Public Health England (PHE) in March 2016. PHE has prepared a report detailing the approaches, methods and decisions made in developing the Eatwell Guide. The report “From Plate to Guide: What, why and how for the Eatwell model” is available on the PHE website.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","58416 ; 58434","2017-01-11T15:25:59.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662869/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662869/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662869/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Health Education: Nutrition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what representations she has received on the Eatwell Guide since March 2016.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","58435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662870","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Secretary of State has regular discussions with Ministerial colleagues on a range of issues, including on air quality.</p><p>Our air quality plans have always followed the best available evidence. We are currently working on the next steps needed to revise the national air quality plan for nitrogen dioxide. We will set out further measures in 2017.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-01-09T14:53:21.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662870/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662870/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662870/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Heathrow Airport: Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Transport on the effect of the proposed third runway at Heathrow Airport on air quality; and what steps her Department is taking to incorporate its assessment of the air quality effect of a third runway in its revised air quality plan.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","58485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662871","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-10","<p>Information on the total amount of current and capital expenditure on services by organisation in Yorkshire and the Humber is publicly available on gov.uk as part of the Country and Regional Analysis statistical release. This information covers 2011-12 through to 2015-16 and can be found at the following web link:</p><p><strong><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/country-and-regional-analysis-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/country-and-regional-analysis-2016</a></strong></p><p>Information specifically on spend on staffing in Yorkshire and the Humber can only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-01-10T15:35:48.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662871/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662871/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662871/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department and its arms-length departmental bodies have spent on (a) staffing, (b) other revenue costs and (c) capital expenditure in the current fiscal year in Yorkshire and the Humber.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","58503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662872","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Waste and Resources Action Programme has published guidance on household food waste collections, which includes advice on the costs and associated benefits of introducing separate food waste collections in England. This guidance is available at: <a href="http://www.wrap.org.uk/content/household-food-waste-collections-guide" target="_blank">http://www.wrap.org.uk/content/household-food-waste-collections-guide</a>. I have not asked the Chief Scientific Adviser to provide additional advice on this matter.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-01-09T15:05:12.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662872/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662872/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662872/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Food: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what advice she has received from the Chief Scientific Adviser to her Department on the cost and associated benefits of introducing separate food waste collections in England.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","58609"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662873","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-09","<p>Defra has not set specific metrics for this industry-led voluntary initiative to improve the quantity and quality of household recycling. The Waste and Resources Action Programme and other members of the industry advisory group for consistency have set out a number of actions and objectives to achieve the vision set out in the Framework and Defra officials will work with them to monitor progress against these actions.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-01-09T15:09:39.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662873/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662873/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662873/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Domestic Waste: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what metrics for success her Department has set for the framework for consistency in household waste collections, launched by WRAP in September 2016.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","58610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662874","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-11","<p>As part of our planning for the UK’s exit from the EU, we are considering the options for reshaping our waste and resources policy and regulatory framework to encourage the more sustainable use of resources. We are currently developing a 25 year environment plan and will consult stakeholders early this year on the priorities for resources, waste and recycling. Views on the key barriers to resource efficiency and ideas for addressing these will be welcome. In parallel, we are working to ensure alignment with other plans in development such as the Government’s new industrial strategy and our emissions reduction plan.</p><p> </p><p>The Environment Agency’s online definition of waste tool is still available. It can be used for a self-assessment of whether a material is a waste or not. The Definition of Waste Panel is closed until further notice while the Environment Agency reviews its role and purpose.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-01-11T15:20:04.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662874/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662874/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662874/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to remove barriers to a more resource-efficient economy; and if she will encourage the Environment Agency to reopen its online definition of waste tool to new submissions.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","58351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662875","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-12","<p>I can confirm my department currently does not have the facility to allow staff to join a credit union through payroll deductions. Staff can still make arrangements to contribute to a credit union via direct debit.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-01-12T12:04:44.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662875/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662875/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662875/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department permits its employees to join a credit union through payroll deductions; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","58450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662876","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-01-11","<p>We meet regularly at Ministerial and official level with representatives of the industry to discuss key issues and opportunities for the UK dairy sector.</p><p> </p><p>I am aware of concerns regarding recommendations on the consumption of dairy products in the Eatwell Guide produced by Public Health England (PHE) in March 2016. PHE has prepared a report detailing the approaches, methods and decisions made in developing the Eatwell Guide. The report “From Plate to Guide: What, why and how for the Eatwell model” is available on the PHE website.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","58434 ; 58435","2017-01-11T15:25:59.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662876/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662876/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662876/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-20","Dairy Farming: Health Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment she has made of the effect of the Eatwell Guide, published in March 2016, on the milk and dairy industry.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","58416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662877","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Secretary of State for Health, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for South West Surrey (Mr Hunt), raised human rights issues in his discussions with Chinese Vice Premier Liu Yandong on 5 December during the UK-China 'People to People' dialogue. Human Rights issues were not raised at the UK-China Economic and Financial Dialogue on 10 November.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-01-09T15:43:10.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662877/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662877/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662877/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","China: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether human rights issues were raised during the recent (a) UK-China Economic and Trade Dialogue and (b) UK-China People to People Dialogue.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","58398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662878","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-12","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office currently does not have the facility to allow staff to join a credit union through payroll deductions. Staff can still make arrangements to contribute to a credit union via direct debit.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-01-12T15:51:00.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662878/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662878/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662878/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department permits its employees to join a credit union through payroll deductions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","58452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662879","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>​I spoke directly to the President-elect, Mr Adama Barrow, to congratulate him on his victory and to offer the UK’s support. We are deeply concerned by President Jammeh’s recent rejection of the elections’ clear and legitimate result and strongly condemn any attempt to disrupt the peaceful, constitutional transfer of power. I also condemned President Jammeh’s refusal to accept the results in a statement on 14 December. We welcome the clear, unified statement of the UN Security Council on 10 December, as well as the efforts of the Economic Community of West African States to impress on President Jammeh the need to respect the will of the people and ensure a peaceful handover of power.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-01-09T14:00:47.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662879/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662879/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662879/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Gambia: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the President of The Gambia on (a) the outcome of the election and (b) protection of democratic rights in that country; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","58438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662880","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>We work with a wide range of partners including other countries in the region and regional institutions to try to improve humanitarian access for all aid agencies in South Sudan.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-01-13T13:43:59.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662880/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662880/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662880/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","South Sudan: International Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 16 November 2016 to Question 52554, who his Department's regional partners are in the facilitation of humanitarian access for aid agencies in South Sudan.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","58348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662881","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>We are aware of recent statements by UN special rapporteurs expressing concern at restrictions placed on human rights defenders and civil society in Egypt. In December, the spokesperson for the then UN Secretary-General, Ban Ki-moon, expressed concern over the arrest of prominent Egyptian human rights defender Azza Soliman.</p><p>We are concerned about the decreasing space for civil society to operate in Egypt. Ministers and senior officials regularly raise our concerns with the Egyptian authorities in both London and Cairo. During my meeting with the Egyptian Ambassador on 8 December, I raised our concerns about the arrest of human rights defender Azza Soliman. In the same meeting I reiterated concerns, outlined in my statement from 1 December, about a proposed new law on Non-Governmental Organisations (NGOs).</p><p>We have also raised our concerns about human rights at the UN. During the most recent session of the UN's Human Rights Council in September we raised concerns about restrictions on civil society in both our national statement and through the EU statement.</p><p>We will continue to monitor the human rights situation in Egypt closely, and to urge the Egyptian government to ensure full implementation of the provisions for the free operation of civil society, contained in the constitution, including through a revised NGO law that conforms to international standards and protects freedom of expression.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-01-13T13:47:01.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662881/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662881/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662881/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Egypt: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the government of Egypt on recent UN reports of human rights abuses in that country.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","58350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662882","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The UK-Tanzania partnership is strong and broad. We are proud of our long standing trade, security and people to people links that bring real benefits to both countries. Our amibition is clear - to work in partnership with Tanzania to increase bilateral trade and investment, support development and generate prosperity and employment for both our countries. ​​We want to help Tanzania achieve its vision of becoming a middle income country.</p><p>Our top priorities are increasing trade and investment, tackling international crime such as corruption, drug trafficking, the illegal wildlife trade and supporting Tanzania's regional lead in bringing peace and security to Burundi.</p><p>Our High Commission in Dar es Salaam maintains close and frequent communication with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Government of Tanzania. Our team in London is also well known to the Tanzanian High Commission.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-01-09T14:21:28.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662882/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662882/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662882/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Tanzania: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the level of political cooperation between the UK and Tanzania.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","58360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662883","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The UK and the Republic of Zambia continue to maintain a close bilateral relationship, with co-operation in a range of areas including development, security, trade and investment and international affairs. Zambian Vice-President Wina Inonge visited London in November 2015 to host an investment conference and my Rt Hon. Friend the former Minister of State for International Development Minister (Nick Hurd) visited Zambia in May 2016. Zambia held elections in August this year; the British High Commission has continued to maintain regular engagement with the Zambian Government since then, focusing particularly on supporting the government with its plans for economic reform.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-01-09T14:24:21.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662883/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662883/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662883/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Zambia: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the level of political cooperation between the UK and Zambia.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","58361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662884","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>We regularly press the Chinese authorities for permission for a Foreign and Commonwealth Office official or Minister to visit the Tibet Autonomous Region (TAR). We last raised this issue with the Chinese authorities at the UK/China Human Rights Dialogue on 27 October. The Chinese have yet to grant our request.</p><p>The last visit by an FCO official to the TAR was in June 2014, and the last Minister to visit was the Hon. Member for Bury South (Mr Lewis) in September 2009.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-01-09T15:42:03.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662884/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662884/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662884/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Tibet: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to secure visits to Tibet by UK diplomatic personnel.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","58397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662885","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>We are deeply concerned by reports that Tashi Rabten was involved in an act of self-immolation in Gansu Province on 8 December, and that members of his family have been detained by the Chinese authorities. We are seeking further information on the situation.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-01-09T15:39:23.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662885/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662885/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662885/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","China: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has raised with the Chinese authorities the detention of the family of Tashi Rabten.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","58394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662886","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>We raised the case of the Tibetan language advocate, Tashi Wangchuk, at the UK-China human rights dialogue, which took place on 27 October. We urged the Chinese authorities to release him from detention.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-01-09T15:40:14.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662886/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662886/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662886/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Tashi Wangchuk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the case of Tashi Wangchuk was raised in the recent UK-China Human Rights Dialogue; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","58395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662887","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>We regularly press the Chinese authorities for permission for a Foreign and Commonwealth Office official or Minister to visit the Tibet Autonomous Region (TAR). We last raised this issue with the Chinese authorities at the UK/China Human Rights Dialogue on 27 October. The Chinese have yet to grant our request.</p><p>The last visit by an FCO official to the TAR was in June 2014, and the last Minister to visit was the Hon. Member for Bury South (Mr Lewis) in September 2009.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-01-09T15:41:16.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662887/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662887/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662887/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Tibet: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will seek to arrange a ministerial visit to Tibet.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","58396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662888","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-12","<p>The UK supports the right of the Falkland Islanders to develop their natural resources for their own economic benefit and I have made this clear to my Argentine counterparts. I welcome the UK-Argentine Joint Statement, agreed during my visit to Argentina in September, in which Argentina agreed that appropriate measures would be taken to remove all obstacles limiting the economic growth and sustainable development of the Falkland Islands, including through the development of its oil and gas industry.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-01-12T16:03:50.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662888/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662888/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662888/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Falkland Islands: Oil","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Argentinian counterpart on UK oil drilling in the Falkland Islands since the beginning of 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","58367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662889","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson) has had no such discussions.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-01-09T16:07:02.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662889/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662889/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662889/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Social Media: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with officials (a) of the European Commission, (b) the EU member states and (c) of the European Parliament on the regulation of social media operators.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","58388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662890","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-12","<p>State Visits are only conducted by Her Majesty the Queen.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-01-12T16:04:59.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662890/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662890/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662890/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Serbia: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what preparations (a) his Department and (b) the British Embassy in Belgrade undertook in advance of his State Visit to Serbia in November 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","58382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662891","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The UK Government has taken every opportunity to raise Mr Tsege’s case at the very highest levels in Ethiopia. The Ethiopian Government are in no doubt about our concern for Mr Tsege and the priority we place on his wellbeing. We have not directly called for Mr Tsege’s release. Britain does not interfere in the legal system of other countries by challenging convictions, any more than we would accept interference in our judicial system. Our priority is to ensure Mr Tsege’s wellbeing and access to legal advice. We believe that calling for his release would not be successful at this stage and could put at risk the progress that has been made, including our access to Mr Tsege.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-01-09T14:08:23.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662891/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662891/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662891/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Andargachew Tsege","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department has formally requested the release of Mr Andargachew Tsege; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","58611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662892","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>Ministers and officials have repeatedly made representations on all consular cases involving British nationals in Iran, including Mr Foroughi's and Mrs Zaghari-Ratcliffe's, at all levels, with the Iranian Government. I raised these cases when I met the Iranian ambassador on 7 December and our ambassador in Iran will continue to raise these cases with the Iranian Government at every available opportunity in Tehran.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-01-13T14:10:36.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662892/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662892/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662892/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Kamal Foroughi and Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 24 November 2016 to Question 53303, what representations the Government has made to the Iranian government on the release of Kamal Foroughi and Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","58595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662893","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The UK's long-standing position, held by successive Governments, is that it is for India and Pakistan to find a lasting resolution to the situation, taking into account the wishes of the Kashmiri people. It is not for the UK to prescribe a solution or to act as a mediator. We encourage both sides to maintain positive dialogue, but the pace and scope of this is for them to determine. During her visit to India in November, my Rt Hon. Friend the Prime Minister the Member for Maidenhead (Mrs May) discussed a range of issues with Prime Minister Modi, including Kashmir. On his trip to Pakistan in November 2016 , my Rt Hon. Friend the Foreign Secretary the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Boris Johnson) reiterated the call for dialogue, while also reiterating that the pace and scope of any dialogue was for India and Pakistan to determine. At that time, he also called for an end to the violence over the Line of Control, and for both sides to exercise restraint.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-01-09T15:46:11.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662893/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662893/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662893/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Kashmir","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to the governments of India and Pakistan on the situation in Kashmir; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","58613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662894","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The murder of Russia's Ambassador to Turkey, Mr Andrei Karlov, on 19 December was a cowardly attack condemned by the Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Boris Johnson) in a statement the same day. Immediately following the shooting, I telephoned the Russian Ambassador to London to offer my own condolences.</p><p>The Prime Minister has written to President Putin to offer her condolences and the Foreign Secretary signed the book of condolence at the Russian Embassy.</p><p>The Foreign Secretary and I have both offered the UK's support to Turkey as they investigate the shooting.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-01-09T15:21:57.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662894/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662894/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662894/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Turkey: Assassination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his (a) Russian and (b) Turkish counterpart on the shooting of the Russian Ambassador to Turkey, Andrei Karlov, in Ankara on 19 December 2016.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","58631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662895","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Government is deeply concerned about the welfare of the Rohingya community in Burma, especially in light of a number of security operations launched in response to the attack on police posts on 9 October. Foreign and Commonwealth Office Ministers and our Ambassador in Rangoon have raised our concerns at the highest levels with the Government of Burma on a number of occasions in recent weeks. On 29 November I raised the issue of the Rohingya with the visiting Burmese Minister for Construction, and relayed calls for the immediate resumption of humanitarian access to Northern Rakhine. I reiterated our call for an independent investigation into allegations of human rights abuses. In a meeting with the Bangladesh High Commissioner, also on 29 November, I welcomed the existing humanitarian assistance provided by the Bangladesh Government to date and urged the government not to return into danger people who seek refuge in Bangladesh.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-01-09T15:44:45.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662895/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662895/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662895/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-20","Bangladesh and Burma: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to the governments of Burma and Bangladesh on the Rohingya people in those countries; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","58612"
